d at Oxford University in 1948, as well as how it related to other presentations Innis made in Britain during the same period. It explores how Innis sought to enrich his analysis by incorporating material related to phenomena such as war, education, religion, culture, geography, and finance. An insightful foreword by Marshall McLuhan is included, as well as bibliographical references and a revised index. By providing a narrative based on extensive notes from Innis, this edition makes Empire and Communications more accessible and contributes to the broad efforts to shape Innis’s legacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommunicationxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aEmpire and Communication.  aGraeco-Roman civilization.  aHarold A. Innis.  aMarshall McLuhan.  aMary Q. Innis.  aalphabet.  acommunications.  amedia history.  amedia studies.  aorality.  apower structures.  aprinting.  awriting.1 aBuxton, William J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuxton, William J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aInnis, Harold A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnis, Mary Q., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLuhan, Marshall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part